-- Paris Club Countries Agree to Reduce Democratic Republic of Congo's Debt
-- B y   J o h n   S i m p s o n
-- 2010-11-17T22:31:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-17/paris-club-countries-agree-to-reduce-democratic-republic-of-congo-s-debt.html
Paris Club creditor countries and
Brazil today agreed to reduce the debt of the Democratic
Republic of Congo by $7.4 billion as a result of the country’s
having achieved its “completion point” on July 1 under the
enhanced initiative for heavily indebted poor countries, the
organization said in a statement on its website.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
